WEBVTT

00:16.755 --> 00:20.890
Julia has... dishonored
her marriage.

00:20.933 --> 00:22.587
[whispers] Who is it?

00:22.631 --> 00:25.329
[Livia] Your father cannot allow
a divorce with Agrippa.

00:25.373 --> 00:28.332
So, you just go and tell them
exactly what I told you.

00:28.376 --> 00:32.597
Porcia--she has agreed
to marry Vilbia for the family.

00:32.641 --> 00:35.035
You will take her back to Rome
and arrange it.

00:35.078 --> 00:36.297
My mother sends you a wife.

00:37.950 --> 00:39.735
[grunts]

00:39.778 --> 00:41.302
What the fuck?

00:41.345 --> 00:43.434
-[Julia] Livia.
-[Antonia] High priestess.

00:43.478 --> 00:45.784
I know Livia well.
We were best friends...

00:45.828 --> 00:47.482
-Turia.
-...when we were children.

00:47.525 --> 00:50.006
She used me and betrayed me,

00:50.050 --> 00:52.487
as she uses
and betrays everyone.

00:52.530 --> 00:54.967
My person is sacrosanct!

00:55.011 --> 00:58.449
Antonia, my daughter,
three births in four years.

00:58.493 --> 01:01.235
You and Vipsania--
not pregnant once.

01:01.278 --> 01:02.236
I need my family
to set an example.

01:02.279 --> 01:03.759
She will.

01:03.802 --> 01:05.935
[Julia] Antonia wants
to kill her husband.

01:05.978 --> 01:08.111
-He scares her.
-You're lying!

01:08.155 --> 01:11.332
-[bone cracks]
-Ow! Aah, aah!

01:11.375 --> 01:13.595
If you think about it,

01:13.638 --> 01:16.640
Domitius is your direct rival
for any kind of power.

01:16.685 --> 01:18.861
When all this is over,
we should talk about the future,

01:18.904 --> 01:21.951
you and me.
Rome needs leaders.

01:21.994 --> 01:24.475
Let's do that.

01:24.519 --> 01:26.782
[Gaius] Tonight we celebrate
the adoption of my grandsons,

01:26.825 --> 01:28.479
the sons of Agrippa.

01:28.523 --> 01:30.481
[Tycho] Is he changing his will?

01:30.525 --> 01:33.484
Agrippa's sons
are next in line to succeed.

01:33.527 --> 01:36.444
Took you long enough
to come through on our deal.

01:36.487 --> 01:38.489
A sacrifice I had to make.

01:38.533 --> 01:40.317
It's all over.

01:40.360 --> 01:41.275
What is?

01:41.318 --> 01:43.799
-Nothing.
-Everything.

01:53.722 --> 02:02.905
♪♪♪

02:14.917 --> 02:16.527
Roman traders.

02:16.571 --> 02:18.355
They passed through the camp
last week.

02:18.399 --> 02:20.531
We told them it was safe.

02:20.575 --> 02:22.490
Where are the rest of them?

02:22.533 --> 02:24.840
[Gaius] Take them down,
make a pyre,

02:24.883 --> 02:26.929
then avenge them.

02:30.585 --> 02:33.762
Let's get you back
over the Rhine.

02:35.372 --> 02:39.159
[horse whinnies]

02:39.202 --> 02:42.684
[indistinct shouting]

02:51.649 --> 02:53.738
Brought you a present.

02:53.781 --> 02:58.439
Tiberius, I thought
you were in the Balkans.

02:58.482 --> 03:00.876
We were.
Mother sends her love.

03:00.919 --> 03:02.486
That won't take up much space.

03:02.530 --> 03:04.445
[laughs]

03:04.488 --> 03:06.229
-So good to see you.
-[Vipsania] You too, Drusus.

03:06.273 --> 03:09.101
Listen.

03:09.145 --> 03:13.584
Do you know
what Stepfather's doing here?

03:15.456 --> 03:17.806
Did he say?

03:17.849 --> 03:19.111
He's supposed to be in Gaul.

03:19.155 --> 03:21.288
He's never been
to Germany before,

03:21.331 --> 03:22.550
and it's a secret.

03:24.813 --> 03:26.771
[whispering] Nobody knows.
Even Mother didn't.

03:26.815 --> 03:30.253
Wow. You've come
all this way to worry.

03:30.297 --> 03:32.299
[normal voice] No, I haven't.

03:32.341 --> 03:35.215
-Yes, he has.
-[chuckles]

03:38.348 --> 03:39.915
[Gaius] What do you think?

03:39.958 --> 03:42.396
What's going on, Tiberius?

03:42.439 --> 03:46.226
He has absolutely
no sense of danger.

03:46.269 --> 03:47.749
What danger?

03:47.792 --> 03:52.667
It's probably nothing.

04:02.503 --> 04:04.418
[Tycho] It's ready.

04:07.203 --> 04:08.770
[door opens and closes]

04:08.813 --> 04:11.773
Your very own ring of Augustus.

04:11.816 --> 04:13.992
[exhales]

04:14.036 --> 04:16.821
Well, it looks
just like the real one.

04:16.865 --> 04:18.692
Yeah, the Greek's a genius.

04:18.736 --> 04:21.608
We're ready now.
We're doing it tomorrow.

04:21.652 --> 04:24.481
Make the arrangements.

04:24.525 --> 04:26.266
Well, we areready, right?

04:26.309 --> 04:28.790
I mean...

04:28.832 --> 04:30.270
Yes.

04:30.313 --> 04:33.490
Oh, you know I don't like it.

04:33.534 --> 04:35.405
People are weird.

04:35.449 --> 04:37.712
They don't do what they should.
They do other stuff instead.

04:37.755 --> 04:39.975
If we get caught,
your exile won't be temporary,

04:40.018 --> 04:42.194
and mine
will be extremely permanent.

04:42.238 --> 04:44.327
Well, Gaius is away.
He may never come back.

04:44.371 --> 04:46.851
I need to know
where his power is going,

04:46.895 --> 04:50.072
what he wants after his death.
I need to see his will.

04:50.115 --> 04:52.204
Which is locked in a vault
in the Temple of Vesta.

04:52.248 --> 04:55.207
-She's an important goddess.
-We've spent months on this.

04:55.251 --> 04:57.209
-I'm not backing out now.
-What if we offend the gods?

04:57.253 --> 05:00.648
Then fuck the gods!

05:00.691 --> 05:02.998
They took everything
from me, everything.

05:03.041 --> 05:05.000
I was a child.

05:05.043 --> 05:06.828
What have I done to them?

05:06.871 --> 05:09.047
Huh? Or anyone?

05:09.091 --> 05:12.224
They never cared about me.

05:12.268 --> 05:15.706
Well,
then I don't care about them.

05:15.750 --> 05:18.579
[theme music playing]

06:07.976 --> 06:12.894
[horse whinnies,
people speaking indistinctly]

06:12.937 --> 06:14.374
Fuck.

06:16.637 --> 06:19.814
-It's the kitchen again.
-Yeah.

06:19.857 --> 06:23.426
Lucky my wife's at the sea.

06:23.470 --> 06:26.777
Could you put me up
for a few days?

06:26.821 --> 06:29.563
-Do I run a boarding house?
-[chuckles]

06:29.606 --> 06:31.303
I'll see you tonight for dinner.

06:34.829 --> 06:36.613
Look at you.

06:36.657 --> 06:39.790
All worried and suspicious,

06:39.834 --> 06:41.618
already snuffling around
for an ulterior motive,

06:41.662 --> 06:43.098
a hidden agenda.

06:43.141 --> 06:45.622
"Is he playing me?"

06:45.666 --> 06:49.321
"Does he want me to think
that he's playing me?"

06:49.365 --> 06:54.675
Or is that the whole point?"

06:54.718 --> 06:57.634
[dog barking]

06:59.941 --> 07:01.116
It's on.

07:01.159 --> 07:02.596
This morning.

07:02.639 --> 07:05.686
Let me know.

07:05.729 --> 07:08.471
It's a bad omen.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.691
No, it's not.

07:19.351 --> 07:23.878
[indistinct conversation]

07:58.433 --> 08:00.480
[door creaks]

08:15.103 --> 08:19.063
I told the High Priestess
I'm visiting my father.

08:19.107 --> 08:22.023
[gasping excitedly]

08:25.417 --> 08:28.464
She's given me
the whole day off.

08:30.988 --> 08:32.381
[seabirds calling]

08:32.424 --> 08:35.688
Iullus.

08:35.732 --> 08:37.734
How was the journey?

08:37.778 --> 08:39.213
Where is everyone?

08:39.256 --> 08:41.912
Oh, not sure about my sister,

08:41.956 --> 08:45.263
but Domitius went with Marcella
to the village hours ago.

08:45.307 --> 08:47.352
And I, of course, thought
the beach was a better option.

08:47.396 --> 08:52.270
Of course. Look.

08:52.314 --> 08:53.620
What is it?

08:53.663 --> 08:55.099
What do you think it is?

08:55.143 --> 08:59.060
We're gonna give it to Domitius.

08:59.103 --> 09:01.236
-What?
-We talked about this.

09:01.279 --> 09:03.064
No, you talked about this!

09:03.107 --> 09:04.805
If you won't do it
to avenge your sister

09:04.848 --> 09:06.502
and save her from
a miserable life with that man,

09:06.546 --> 09:07.895
then at least do it
for yourself.

09:07.938 --> 09:09.461
I invited him down here

09:09.505 --> 09:11.115
to talk about
the future of Rome.

09:11.159 --> 09:12.639
That's perfect.
He won't suspect a thing!

09:12.682 --> 09:14.554
Which would be easier
if he wasn't dead!

09:14.597 --> 09:17.252
And this is the ideal place.

09:17.295 --> 09:19.776
Out of town,
away from the doctors.

09:19.820 --> 09:21.778
It's how
Livia did it with Marcellus.

09:21.822 --> 09:25.652
[Iullus scoffs]

09:25.695 --> 09:29.264
Domitius stands between you
and everything you want.

09:29.307 --> 09:32.528
Or everything
you say you want.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.486
He--he broke
your sister's finger,

09:34.530 --> 09:36.314
and she was protecting us.

09:36.358 --> 09:37.620
Are you just gonna let that go?

09:43.017 --> 09:46.324
What is it?

09:46.368 --> 09:49.197
Capria's cousin knows a woman,

09:49.240 --> 09:53.244
over by the Aurelian Gate.

09:53.288 --> 09:55.943
Come on.

09:55.986 --> 09:58.075
I wanna show you something.

09:58.119 --> 10:00.121
What?

10:00.164 --> 10:01.601
Where are you going?

10:01.644 --> 10:03.864
Iullus, give it back to me.

10:03.907 --> 10:07.563
You do realize that if you
poison anyone in this family,

10:07.607 --> 10:09.652
everyone will think
it was Livia.

10:09.696 --> 10:12.263
-No, they won't.
-[scoffs]

10:12.307 --> 10:14.004
And?

10:14.048 --> 10:17.704
And have you
no sense of gratitude?

10:17.747 --> 10:19.183
After what she did for us?

10:19.227 --> 10:20.837
She was desperate
to get back to Rome.

10:20.881 --> 10:22.317
She practically used us.

10:22.360 --> 10:25.146
You're right.

10:25.189 --> 10:27.627
Come on.

10:27.670 --> 10:29.498
What?

10:29.541 --> 10:32.022
Where are you going?

10:32.066 --> 10:36.548
Iullus! What?

10:36.592 --> 10:39.508
I wanted to show you
what I thought of your plan.

10:39.551 --> 10:43.077
What is wrong with you?

10:44.556 --> 10:47.168
-Fucking idiot!
-Julia!

10:47.211 --> 10:52.521
[gasping, grunting]

10:52.564 --> 10:54.044
Ha!

10:54.088 --> 10:56.220
Look what I have!

10:56.264 --> 10:58.919
I've got it!
Come and get it!

10:58.962 --> 11:02.618
Oh, wait, I forgot you can't,
'cause you can't fucking swim,

11:02.662 --> 11:03.880
'cause you're afraid
of the water,

11:03.924 --> 11:06.230
as well as everything else!

11:06.274 --> 11:08.319
What's the matter, eh?

11:08.363 --> 11:11.671
Rent boy! Fucking pig!

11:11.714 --> 11:14.064
Fucking jizz mouth, cocksucker!

11:14.108 --> 11:16.371
Here it is! Here it is!

11:16.414 --> 11:18.199
[gasps]

11:18.242 --> 11:21.158
Here what is?

11:21.202 --> 11:22.769
[gasps]

11:22.812 --> 11:26.642
-Is that Augustus' daughter?
-Yes. Yes it is.

11:28.426 --> 11:32.213
[gasping]

11:32.256 --> 11:34.258
Hello.

11:34.302 --> 11:37.174
What was she
waving around in her hand?

11:37.218 --> 11:38.219
[grunts]

11:38.262 --> 11:39.742
[Iullus] Oh, you know Julia.

11:39.786 --> 11:41.613
Hello, Gallus.

11:41.657 --> 11:43.659
-[Iullus] Antonia.
-[Antonia] What's going on?

11:43.703 --> 11:47.054
Look, Julia, you remember
Gaius Assinius Gallus.

11:47.097 --> 11:49.230
Fuck off.

11:53.277 --> 11:55.584
[gasps]

11:55.627 --> 12:00.415
[continues gasping]

12:00.458 --> 12:06.464
[breathing heavily]

12:06.508 --> 12:12.079
That was amazing.

12:12.122 --> 12:15.256
The gods.

12:15.299 --> 12:19.651
[Porcia] Who are you?

12:19.695 --> 12:21.262
What are you doing
in my bedroom? Get out!

12:21.305 --> 12:22.959
Sorry to intrude.

12:23.003 --> 12:25.179
But on the bright side,
I'm not your husband.

12:25.222 --> 12:26.963
Men are so intolerant
when their wives get caught

12:27.007 --> 12:31.185
in vile and deviant
sexual practices.

12:31.228 --> 12:33.796
Who are you,
and what do you want?

12:33.840 --> 12:35.842
I want you to leave.

12:35.885 --> 12:40.672
[whispers] It's all right. Go.

12:55.209 --> 12:59.126
Unfortunately, Aurelia, your
situation is much more serious.

12:59.169 --> 13:02.869
When you joined
the Temple of Vesta,

13:02.912 --> 13:06.524
you took a vow of chastity for
the duration of your service.

13:06.568 --> 13:10.006
As you know, any priestess
dishonoring that vow

13:10.050 --> 13:12.139
is buried alive.

13:12.182 --> 13:16.317
Why are you telling me this?

13:16.360 --> 13:19.886
'Cause I'm your friend.

13:19.929 --> 13:21.844
And I'm going to make sure
nobody ever finds out

13:21.888 --> 13:24.716
what you've done.

13:24.760 --> 13:28.851
In return,
all you have to do

13:28.895 --> 13:32.333
is borrow a will
from the vault of the temple

13:32.376 --> 13:35.205
and bring it to the Senate House
in the fourth hour tomorrow.

13:35.249 --> 13:36.946
Then, a day or so later,

13:36.990 --> 13:40.210
simply pick it up from
the same place and return it.

13:40.254 --> 13:43.344
-What will?
-The will of Caesar Augustus.

13:43.387 --> 13:46.260
[scoffs]

13:46.303 --> 13:47.739
I can't do that.

13:47.783 --> 13:50.220
Make no mistake.

13:50.264 --> 13:52.222
I will denounce you
to the Chief Vestal

13:52.266 --> 13:53.658
without a second thought.

13:53.702 --> 13:55.051
Witnesses will come forward,

13:55.095 --> 13:56.574
slaves will testify.
-No, no.

13:56.618 --> 13:58.228
-And everyone knows...
-No!

13:58.272 --> 14:01.623
...how strictly Turia enforces
the rules of your Order.

14:03.930 --> 14:06.367
Yeah.

14:06.410 --> 14:07.890
[exhales]

14:10.110 --> 14:12.590
You'll bring it straight back?

14:12.634 --> 14:15.724
And you'll never
hear from me again.

14:17.595 --> 14:20.076
-[Porcia] Livia.
-How did it go?

14:20.120 --> 14:22.078
It went pretty well,
while I was there.

14:22.122 --> 14:24.298
I do feel bad
about the girl, though.

14:24.341 --> 14:26.561
-Well, you made her happy.
-[scoffs]

14:26.604 --> 14:30.130
Until I didn't.

14:30.173 --> 14:33.873
So, do you want to tell me
what it's all about now?

14:33.915 --> 14:35.875
It's better you don't know.

14:35.918 --> 14:39.095
It's obviously to do with Turia.

14:39.139 --> 14:41.576
Your ancient feud
with the High Priestess,

14:41.619 --> 14:45.145
it's legendary.

14:45.188 --> 14:47.234
Are you sure you don't want me
to find you a husband?

14:47.277 --> 14:49.105
[scoffs]

14:49.149 --> 14:50.498
Fuck, no.

14:50.540 --> 14:52.935
What do I need one of them for?

14:52.979 --> 14:55.155
It's still a form of slavery,

14:55.198 --> 14:57.287
even if they don't own you
outright any more.

14:57.331 --> 15:00.247
And the money you gave me
has made me independent.

15:00.290 --> 15:03.859
I do what I like,
I sleep where I want,

15:03.903 --> 15:06.514
and I never have to see
my fucking guardian again.

15:13.042 --> 15:14.130
I won't forget it.

15:14.174 --> 15:16.306
[door opens]

15:21.181 --> 15:25.098
-Nice.
-You, too.

15:25.141 --> 15:26.795
Priestess says she'll do it.

15:29.798 --> 15:32.670
[breathing heavily]

16:20.675 --> 16:24.809
[panting]

16:24.853 --> 16:27.073
Oh, come on, hurry up.

16:27.116 --> 16:32.034
Antonia has an announcement,
and I came ages ago.

16:32.078 --> 16:33.644
Go on.

16:33.688 --> 16:37.866
[gasping continues]

17:01.933 --> 17:04.588
[Antonia] Now everyone's here.

17:04.632 --> 17:06.415
I have some news.

17:06.460 --> 17:08.243
[Julia] Keep it coming.

17:08.288 --> 17:10.724
I'm pregnant.

17:10.768 --> 17:12.988
[gasps]

17:15.598 --> 17:17.079
Pregnant.

17:17.123 --> 17:18.950
Well, it only took you
five years.

17:18.993 --> 17:20.082
Well done, Antonia.

17:20.126 --> 17:21.953
Stand up.

17:26.306 --> 17:27.436
[exhales deeply]

17:32.312 --> 17:34.879
[under breath] And we all
thought he was a eunuch.

17:34.923 --> 17:36.577
Thank you.

17:39.101 --> 17:41.147
I can't wait to tell your uncle.

17:43.410 --> 17:46.761
Domitius, I'll be sure to make
a sacrifice to your health...

17:46.804 --> 17:49.285
Make sure
it doesn't happen to you.

17:49.329 --> 17:50.939
[Gallus] ...and to your future.

17:50.982 --> 17:53.768
Oh, I know
you're fucking Gallus.

17:53.811 --> 17:56.292
That's the only reason
why you're down here.

17:56.336 --> 17:58.816
-I remember my uncle.
-What's your point?

17:58.860 --> 18:02.603
If he gets you pregnant,
you're on your own.

18:06.868 --> 18:10.480
Antonia, Domitius,
congratulations!

18:10.524 --> 18:12.787
[chuckles]

18:12.830 --> 18:15.006
I think I should join her.

18:15.050 --> 18:17.661
[Domitius] We'll, er,
speak tomorrow.

18:17.705 --> 18:19.446
-[Iullus] Yes, let's do that.
-[Antonia] Hey...

18:19.489 --> 18:21.491
[Iullus]
Anytime is fine for me.

18:21.535 --> 18:23.319
Are you not happy for me?

18:23.363 --> 18:26.627
Sure.

18:26.670 --> 18:29.020
[gasps]

18:29.064 --> 18:33.286
[indistinct conversation
continues in background]

18:37.072 --> 18:39.074
Oh, look, Julia,
here come your children.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.728
See if you can recognize
any of them.

18:46.690 --> 18:48.562
[Agrippa] You're in a good mood.

18:48.605 --> 18:49.824
[Livia chuckles]

18:49.867 --> 18:52.131
What have you been up to?

18:52.174 --> 18:55.699
Oh, you know, the usual.

18:55.743 --> 18:57.484
[Agrippa scoffs]

19:00.878 --> 19:04.708
How are things
with you and Julia?

19:04.752 --> 19:08.103
-Well, how about you and Gaius?
-I asked you first.

19:16.111 --> 19:19.723
It didn't make me feel better,

19:19.767 --> 19:22.552
killing the man
she was sleeping with.

19:22.596 --> 19:27.122
I thought it would,
but... it didn't.

19:28.950 --> 19:31.692
Ah, you got
your boys adopted, though.

19:31.735 --> 19:35.217
Are you suggesting that made
my wife's infidelity worthwhile?

19:35.261 --> 19:37.611
I'm just saying
it's much more important.

19:40.135 --> 19:43.051
Does it ever bother you
that he adopted my two sons

19:43.094 --> 19:45.009
and never yours?

19:45.053 --> 19:46.924
-Why would it?
-Oh, come on.

19:46.968 --> 19:50.232
-What?
-Don't play me.

19:50.276 --> 19:53.453
-You love power more than life.
-[scoffs] Yes, and?

19:53.496 --> 19:54.802
Well, perhaps you want Drusus

19:54.845 --> 19:57.413
to be the next First Citizen,
for example.

19:57.457 --> 20:00.416
Oh, he doesn't have the ambition
or the brains.

20:00.460 --> 20:03.071
Yeah, but you
have plenty to spare.

20:03.114 --> 20:06.074
Well... yes.

20:06.117 --> 20:10.557
[both chuckle]

20:10.600 --> 20:12.646
Listen...

20:14.604 --> 20:17.303
I want you
to promise me something.

20:17.346 --> 20:22.221
When I die, I want you
to look after my kids,

20:22.264 --> 20:24.440
especially the boys.

20:24.484 --> 20:26.790
[exhales]

20:26.834 --> 20:28.792
What if I go first?

20:28.836 --> 20:31.491
Well, I'll look after your two,
but you know that.

20:34.015 --> 20:36.017
You'd do the same for me?

20:39.325 --> 20:40.630
[exhales]

20:40.674 --> 20:41.979
Of course I will.

20:45.156 --> 20:47.507
Okay.

20:51.554 --> 20:54.470
[mysterious music plays]

20:54.514 --> 20:57.430
♪♪♪

21:03.305 --> 21:07.701
[crying]

21:09.833 --> 21:11.531
[whispers] Fuck.

21:11.574 --> 21:14.490
-Turia.
-Aurelia.

21:14.534 --> 21:17.319
May I speak with you, please?

21:32.769 --> 21:34.858
On the way
to visit my father today,

21:34.902 --> 21:37.731
I was stopped
in the street by a man.

21:37.774 --> 21:40.734
I'd never seen him before,
but he knew who I was.

21:42.431 --> 21:44.694
He said he wanted me
to do something,

21:44.738 --> 21:47.828
and if I didn't do it,
he would come to you

21:47.871 --> 21:50.134
and denounce me
for breaking my vows...

21:50.178 --> 21:54.356
with women.

21:54.400 --> 21:56.532
It was disgusting.

21:56.576 --> 22:01.058
He said that
he would produce witnesses

22:01.102 --> 22:03.017
and that you
would have no choice

22:03.060 --> 22:04.584
but to condemn me.

22:04.627 --> 22:07.369
Who was this?

22:13.897 --> 22:16.030
Just a man.

22:16.073 --> 22:18.249
Tall, good-looking,

22:18.293 --> 22:20.426
with dark skin
and a shaved head.

22:20.469 --> 22:22.471
And what did he want you to do?

22:22.515 --> 22:27.128
He told me to take the will
of Augustus out of the vault

22:27.171 --> 22:30.697
and bring it to him
at the Senate House tomorrow.

22:30.740 --> 22:33.090
He'd then meet me again
afterwards to return it.

22:33.134 --> 22:35.789
Nobody would ever have known
it was gone.

22:39.401 --> 22:41.272
Augustus will be very grateful

22:41.316 --> 22:43.274
to hear about this plot
against him.

22:47.409 --> 22:49.063
But in the meantime,

22:49.106 --> 22:54.155
this must remain
just between us.

22:56.810 --> 23:00.248
Tomorrow I want you
to take his will to the Senate,

23:00.291 --> 23:03.120
just as you were told.

23:03.164 --> 23:06.733
You can leave
everything else to me.

23:13.261 --> 23:15.872
[Aurelia] Step away from me.

23:15.916 --> 23:17.483
[horse whinnies]

23:34.848 --> 23:37.633
[indistinct conversations
in background]

24:01.352 --> 24:04.704
♪♪♪

24:27.727 --> 24:30.730
For the Domina.

24:46.572 --> 24:52.403
So how do you read Augustus'
intentions for the succession?

24:52.447 --> 24:54.449
[Domitius] It's clear to me
he wants the two sons

24:54.493 --> 24:58.061
he adopted from Agrippa
to go on with his work,

24:58.105 --> 24:59.715
protect his legacy.

24:59.759 --> 25:00.716
Yes, but they're young.

25:00.760 --> 25:04.111
They're what? Four and one.

25:04.154 --> 25:06.853
And if anything should happen
to him or Agrippa,

25:06.896 --> 25:09.377
then it's obvious someone
would need to step in

25:09.420 --> 25:11.422
to look after things.

25:11.466 --> 25:15.688
Of course,
until they came of age.

25:18.952 --> 25:22.042
Where do you think
Drusus and Tiberius stand?

25:22.085 --> 25:24.261
Near a door.

25:24.305 --> 25:26.089
Drusus has no interest
in politics,

25:26.133 --> 25:28.527
and Tiberius
has even less than that.

25:31.094 --> 25:32.443
All right.

25:35.316 --> 25:38.449
[Julia] I am happy
for you and the baby.

25:40.451 --> 25:44.107
I know.

25:44.151 --> 25:47.763
We're finished, you know--
me and Iullus.

25:47.807 --> 25:51.550
What? No.

25:51.593 --> 25:54.944
You've loved him all your life.

25:54.988 --> 25:56.598
Not anymore.

25:56.642 --> 25:59.122
You've said that before.

25:59.166 --> 26:01.951
It's over.

26:01.995 --> 26:03.823
I don't believe you.

26:03.866 --> 26:06.477
-Done.
-I don't... believe you.

26:06.521 --> 26:09.045
Antonia, I am serious.

26:09.089 --> 26:12.788
Fuck! Fuck!

26:12.832 --> 26:15.617
The will. This won't do.

26:15.661 --> 26:18.011
[panting]

26:18.054 --> 26:21.449
I'll make the arrangements.

26:21.492 --> 26:23.364
[exhales]

26:37.378 --> 26:38.640
I'll be back tonight.

26:46.039 --> 26:49.433
[Turia] And you're quite sure
you saw the man with the bag

26:49.477 --> 26:52.001
come in the side of this house?

26:52.045 --> 26:54.134
[girl] Yes, High Priestess,
I'm sure.

26:54.177 --> 26:56.179
May I help you High Priestess?

26:56.223 --> 27:00.183
I'm Tycho, I run
the household for Augustus.

27:00.227 --> 27:02.882
Yes, I suppose
you aregood-looking.

27:04.623 --> 27:07.495
But you must know Augustus
is away from Rome at the moment.

27:07.538 --> 27:10.150
Is his wife at home?

27:10.193 --> 27:12.848
She went riding.

27:12.892 --> 27:15.155
But I'm expecting her back
tonight.

27:15.198 --> 27:18.332
Ask her to call on me
at the Temple

27:18.375 --> 27:21.074
at her earliest convenience.

27:23.511 --> 27:26.035
May I ask what it concerns?

27:26.079 --> 27:32.215
She knows very well
what it concerns, and so do you.

27:37.917 --> 27:39.832
[exhales deeply]

27:39.875 --> 27:43.183
-[door closes]
-[under breath] Fuck.

27:43.226 --> 27:45.402
[Livia] I saw his will.

27:45.446 --> 27:47.361
[horse whinnies,
chicken clucks]

27:48.623 --> 27:49.842
Gaius' will.

27:49.885 --> 27:51.408
What?

27:51.452 --> 27:53.584
How the fuck
did you manage that?

27:53.628 --> 27:57.545
Isn't it locked up
with all the Vestals?

27:57.588 --> 27:59.547
Oh, you didn't.

27:59.590 --> 28:03.159
[exhales] How bad is it?

28:03.203 --> 28:07.207
[sighs]

28:07.250 --> 28:11.254
Oh, help yourself. Oi!

28:11.298 --> 28:15.215
So, the adopted sons of Agrippa
inherit everything, eh?

28:15.258 --> 28:16.564
Well, we expected that.

28:16.607 --> 28:18.479
It was you
who got them adopted.

28:18.522 --> 28:21.787
-Who's the executor?
-Domitius.

28:21.830 --> 28:24.050
What, even though you slimed him
for Julia's infidelity?

28:24.093 --> 28:25.442
I know.

28:25.486 --> 28:27.749
No mention of Drusus
and Tiberius?

28:27.793 --> 28:29.708
Nothing.

28:29.751 --> 28:31.797
It's Agrippa
or fucking Domitius

28:31.840 --> 28:34.974
to ensure the proper
administration of the state,

28:35.017 --> 28:37.890
until the boys come of age.

28:37.933 --> 28:42.068
And how about you?
Did you get anything?

28:42.111 --> 28:43.460
Oh, come on!

28:43.504 --> 28:45.419
He's not dead yet.

28:45.462 --> 28:47.116
A lot can change.
It means nothing.

28:47.160 --> 28:50.380
It means that the only thing
that matters to him

28:50.424 --> 28:52.339
is blood--his blood.

28:52.382 --> 28:53.819
Well, he was always like that.

28:53.862 --> 28:55.472
Well, I thought he--
he'd grow up.

28:55.516 --> 28:59.955
You know, that's not the way
you run a state.

28:59.999 --> 29:01.957
There has to be a place
for merit somewhere,

29:02.001 --> 29:04.177
you know, ability, experience.

29:04.220 --> 29:06.614
You can't just hand it all
to the first thing

29:06.657 --> 29:08.485
that comes out
of your daughter's vagina.

29:08.529 --> 29:13.360
Well, you can if you're a king,
and you made him that, so...

29:13.403 --> 29:16.493
Livia!
Are you staying for dinner?

29:16.537 --> 29:17.799
We done a goat in this morning.

29:17.843 --> 29:20.759
[laughter]

29:20.802 --> 29:22.151
Mmm.

29:22.195 --> 29:23.587
-Is that another new dress?
-Oh, yeah.

29:23.631 --> 29:25.633
Look, getting back to Domitius,

29:25.676 --> 29:28.157
when are we gonna use
what we have on him, hmm?

29:28.201 --> 29:31.813
[sighs] When we need to.

29:42.563 --> 29:43.477
[seabirds calling]

29:43.520 --> 29:45.174
Hi.

29:45.218 --> 29:49.788
For once in your consistently
miserable life, Marcella,

29:49.831 --> 29:51.485
you seem almost happy.

29:51.528 --> 29:55.402
Well, I just had Gallus
in the woods again.

29:55.445 --> 29:58.622
Cuckolding Iullus
always cheers me up.

29:58.666 --> 30:01.321
In itself it's... it's simple,

30:01.364 --> 30:07.631
yet, somehow, richly satisfying
in a very profound way.

30:07.675 --> 30:09.720
Is that the key to serenity?

30:09.764 --> 30:11.374
Cuckolding Iullus?

30:11.418 --> 30:13.855
A total lack of ambition.

30:13.899 --> 30:15.857
Hmm.

30:15.901 --> 30:18.251
It's the secret to a long life.

30:19.730 --> 30:21.428
[Domitius scoffs]

30:23.473 --> 30:26.346
[ominous music playing]

30:26.389 --> 30:30.176
♪♪♪

30:30.219 --> 30:33.092
[Drusus] Well, it's easy enough
to get into Germany.

30:33.135 --> 30:36.356
The tribes run and scatter.
They take weeks to form an army.

30:36.399 --> 30:38.358
But then they
try to stop you leaving.

30:38.401 --> 30:41.752
The ambush is their thing.

30:41.796 --> 30:44.755
They know where to wait,
and they can wait for days.

30:44.799 --> 30:46.932
Then they pour javelins
into your columns and retreat.

30:46.975 --> 30:48.455
Then they reload and come again.

30:48.498 --> 30:53.068
Their men fight naked, mostly.
Except for boots.

30:53.112 --> 30:55.897
Kings and chiefs wear trousers.

30:55.941 --> 30:56.898
Trousers?

30:56.942 --> 30:58.813
I know.

30:58.857 --> 31:01.947
Certainly, it's no place
for fashion.

31:01.990 --> 31:07.300
But, in many respects,
their culture is very advanced.

31:07.343 --> 31:08.779
Women are honored,

31:08.823 --> 31:11.913
and they are free to marry
anyone they like.

31:11.957 --> 31:13.610
Men rely on them to make

31:13.654 --> 31:17.136
all the very important decisions
on behalf of the tribe.

31:17.179 --> 31:18.702
Luckily, that could
never happen in Rome.

31:18.746 --> 31:21.662
[laughter]

31:24.143 --> 31:25.840
[Gaius] Listen, Drusus.

31:25.884 --> 31:27.711
There's something
I want you to do for me,

31:27.755 --> 31:31.628
but I wanted to ask you myself.

31:31.672 --> 31:33.587
I don't want you
to go into Germany

31:33.630 --> 31:36.764
to avenge those merchants.

31:36.807 --> 31:39.332
I want you to go into Germany

31:39.375 --> 31:42.161
and stay there.

31:42.204 --> 31:47.949
I want you to take Germany,

31:47.993 --> 31:55.130
from the Rhine
to the Elbe, for Rome.

31:55.174 --> 31:57.654
A sacred quest.

31:57.698 --> 31:59.004
The first province
since my father, Julius Caesar,

31:59.047 --> 32:01.180
conquered Gaul.

32:04.357 --> 32:08.535
I want you to make history.

32:11.146 --> 32:12.669
[Vipsania] But what's the point?

32:12.713 --> 32:15.020
It's just forest and swamp.

32:15.063 --> 32:18.675
And for some reason, the people
seem to resent being slaves.

32:18.719 --> 32:21.113
I hope Domitius
won't be offended

32:21.156 --> 32:23.854
that you're preferring
my brother like this.

32:23.898 --> 32:28.033
He's senior,
I know, and capable,

32:28.076 --> 32:30.383
and I am fond of him.

32:30.426 --> 32:34.169
But I just think...

32:34.213 --> 32:38.652
Drusus has earned it.

32:41.350 --> 32:43.135
To Drusus.

32:43.178 --> 32:44.223
[Antonina] To Drusus.

32:44.266 --> 32:46.877
[Gaius]
Good fortune, Drusus.

32:53.014 --> 32:54.711
[Drusus] What the fuck?

32:54.755 --> 32:56.191
What were you talking
about Domitius?

32:56.235 --> 32:57.323
This is a fucking
enormous honor!

32:57.366 --> 32:58.715
-No, it isn't.
-Yes, it is.

32:58.759 --> 33:00.326
It's a ten-year suicide note,
is what it is.

33:00.369 --> 33:02.371
-What? No, it isn't.
-Yes, it is!

33:02.415 --> 33:04.025
And I'd be asking yourself
why it's got your name on it.

33:04.069 --> 33:06.419
My... job

33:06.462 --> 33:08.029
is to bring glory
for our family,

33:08.073 --> 33:10.597
because that leads
to everything else.

33:10.640 --> 33:13.687
Your job is to stay alive,

33:13.730 --> 33:17.038
otherwise everything else
leads to nowhere.

33:17.082 --> 33:18.213
[scoffs] If I didn't
know you better,

33:18.257 --> 33:19.954
I'd say you were jealous.

33:22.870 --> 33:28.919
[laughing]

33:28.963 --> 33:32.401
[chuckles]

33:32.445 --> 33:38.886
All right, listen,
you beautiful idiot.

33:38.929 --> 33:41.410
This is a mad undertaking...

33:41.454 --> 33:43.369
and thoroughly dangerous.

33:43.412 --> 33:46.198
If you do pull it off,

33:46.241 --> 33:48.591
Stepfather will take the glory.

33:50.158 --> 33:54.032
If it dies
screaming in a swamp,

33:54.075 --> 33:56.773
you'll take the blame.

33:56.817 --> 33:58.471
[Antonina] Wait a minute.

33:58.514 --> 34:03.650
So, you're saying what, exactly?

34:03.693 --> 34:06.566
That this is some kind of trap?

34:06.609 --> 34:09.743
-I know my uncle.
-No one knows your uncle.

34:09.786 --> 34:12.659
Not even Mother.

34:12.702 --> 34:15.922
You two are up to something,

34:15.966 --> 34:18.665
and you never
tell us what it is.

34:18.708 --> 34:24.279
Yes, 'cause they know
it will break our hearts.

34:24.322 --> 34:26.455
All right.

34:26.498 --> 34:29.676
What do you want me to do?
Tell him I'm busy?

34:29.719 --> 34:33.418
No, of course not. Just...

34:33.462 --> 34:36.944
I'll talk to Mother...

34:36.987 --> 34:38.902
Just...

34:38.946 --> 34:43.123
Don't die in the meantime.

34:43.168 --> 34:45.692
[scoffs]

34:55.831 --> 34:58.531
[horse nickers]

35:01.229 --> 35:02.491
[Livia] What?

35:02.535 --> 35:05.364
[Tycho] I don't know how to...

35:05.407 --> 35:07.322
We're fucked.

35:07.366 --> 35:09.063
Already?

35:16.026 --> 35:18.899
[indistinct conversation]

35:28.604 --> 35:30.737
I've been expecting you...

35:34.044 --> 35:36.395
for 20 years.

35:55.283 --> 35:57.067
May I offer you some wine?

35:57.111 --> 35:59.374
No, thank you.

35:59.418 --> 36:01.768
Oh, I think
you're going to need it.

36:17.653 --> 36:20.569
I was young and in love.

36:20.613 --> 36:23.398
It never occurred to me
you didn't love me back.

36:23.442 --> 36:27.576
So when you asked me
all those years ago,

36:27.620 --> 36:29.883
if I could borrow
the will of Marcus Antonius

36:29.926 --> 36:31.406
from the vault,

36:31.450 --> 36:34.061
just so your husband
could read it,

36:34.104 --> 36:35.628
I believed you.

36:35.671 --> 36:40.110
And when you told me
you'd bring it straight back,

36:40.154 --> 36:42.156
it never occurred to me
you were lying.

36:43.984 --> 36:45.638
Because we were best friends.

36:45.681 --> 36:48.293
And I loved you.

36:55.648 --> 36:59.434
I was stripped naked
in front of the whole Order

36:59.478 --> 37:02.089
and whipped
until my back was bloody.

37:04.178 --> 37:06.789
But none of that,
none of it...

37:06.833 --> 37:11.968
hurt anywhere near as much
as your betrayal

37:12.012 --> 37:13.013
and abandonment.

37:15.668 --> 37:18.453
And now here you are...

37:18.497 --> 37:20.542
at it again.

37:20.586 --> 37:26.940
I very much doubt you want your
husband to find out this time.

37:26.983 --> 37:28.637
What do you want?

37:32.989 --> 37:37.603
I've served as a Vestal
for nearly 30 years.

37:37.646 --> 37:41.084
In a few months, my time is up.

37:41.128 --> 37:43.478
I want to enjoy life,

37:43.522 --> 37:47.787
which will take
more than my pension.

37:47.830 --> 37:50.790
I want your estates

37:50.833 --> 37:57.449
in Italy, Greece, and Egypt.

37:57.492 --> 38:00.016
All of them.

38:00.060 --> 38:05.544
In return for my silence,
I want everything you have.

38:08.373 --> 38:11.289
[ominous music plays]

38:11.332 --> 38:15.031
♪♪♪

38:15.075 --> 38:17.860
You were right. We're fucked.

38:17.904 --> 38:19.471
Aurelia gave us up.

38:19.514 --> 38:21.211
Turia wants the will back,
I presume?

38:21.255 --> 38:24.345
[sighs] Tomorrow morning.

38:24.389 --> 38:27.043
[exhales]

38:38.141 --> 38:41.536
So, um,
how's the kitchen coming?

38:41.580 --> 38:44.626
Ooh, now you're in a bad mood.

38:44.670 --> 38:48.369
[exhales]

38:48.413 --> 38:51.285
What happened today?

38:51.329 --> 38:55.768
I've been thinking
about that time you and me

38:55.811 --> 38:59.859
got the will from the Temple.

38:59.902 --> 39:01.251
And why the gloom?

39:01.295 --> 39:05.081
That was your breakthrough.

39:05.125 --> 39:07.867
Your first great triumph.

39:07.910 --> 39:09.869
That was
the start of everything,

39:09.912 --> 39:12.741
for Gaius, for me, and for you.

39:12.785 --> 39:16.092
When you put that will
up in the Forum,

39:16.136 --> 39:18.617
it destroyed Marcus Antonius,

39:18.660 --> 39:20.967
wanting to be buried in Egypt,

39:21.010 --> 39:23.448
leaving everything to Cleopatra.

39:23.491 --> 39:26.364
A year later, he was dead,
Cleopatra, too.

39:26.407 --> 39:29.715
-I liked her.
-[laughs]

39:29.758 --> 39:31.107
You would.

39:31.151 --> 39:34.110
-She had guts.
-Mm-hmm.

39:34.154 --> 39:38.550
And after that,
Gaius was the only one left.

39:38.593 --> 39:41.596
The master of the world.

39:41.640 --> 39:46.079
Everything he has,
everything he is,

39:46.122 --> 39:49.996
he owes to that will.

39:50.039 --> 39:56.306
And it didn't cost a thing.

39:56.350 --> 40:00.093
The bill just arrived.

40:00.136 --> 40:05.228
What?

40:05.272 --> 40:07.796
I fucked up, Agrippa.

40:12.366 --> 40:15.630
Hey! Tell me!

40:15.674 --> 40:17.458
Whatever it is,
I'll deal with it.

40:17.502 --> 40:18.807
No, you can't!

40:18.851 --> 40:20.766
[breathing heavily]

40:20.809 --> 40:23.769
Not this.

40:25.423 --> 40:28.817
-Not even you.
-Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

40:28.861 --> 40:31.516
Is someone coming for you?
After all this time?

40:31.559 --> 40:34.693
Who? Who is it? Tell me who!

40:34.736 --> 40:36.782
Whoever it is,
I'll deal with them.

40:36.825 --> 40:40.873
You know I will. Hey.

41:07.029 --> 41:09.249
[whispers]
Are you playing me, Livia?

41:14.341 --> 41:15.560
[whispers] I don't know.

41:20.042 --> 41:21.653
I'm sorry.

41:30.575 --> 41:33.491
[gasping]

41:50.899 --> 41:53.772
[grunting]

42:00.561 --> 42:01.910
[laughs]

42:01.954 --> 42:04.913
[grunting]

42:04.957 --> 42:08.090
[Julia] How did it go...

42:08.134 --> 42:09.744
with Domitius yesterday?

42:09.788 --> 42:13.661
[birds calling]

42:13.705 --> 42:16.925
Did you find out everything
Livia wanted to know?

42:18.579 --> 42:21.930
[scoffs] Come on, Iullus.

42:21.974 --> 42:24.803
You wouldn't dare
make a move without Livia.

42:24.846 --> 42:27.719
And rightly so, of course.

42:27.762 --> 42:30.156
Track record in politics.

42:30.199 --> 42:33.289
She had you
invite him down here,

42:33.333 --> 42:36.597
told you what to say,

42:36.641 --> 42:39.208
and now you're
going to report back.

42:39.252 --> 42:41.907
But he isn't stupid.

42:41.950 --> 42:43.909
And neither is she.

42:43.952 --> 42:46.215
Neither of them trust you,

42:46.259 --> 42:48.261
and when the time comes,

42:48.304 --> 42:52.439
you'll be floating
down the Tiber.

42:52.482 --> 42:54.267
Give it up, baby.

42:54.310 --> 42:56.312
Seriously.

42:58.706 --> 43:00.926
Open a whore house.

43:03.319 --> 43:06.627
It wasn't poison...

43:06.671 --> 43:09.151
you had.

43:12.024 --> 43:17.072
The woman that Capria's cousin
knows over by the Aurelian Gate,

43:17.116 --> 43:22.817
she sells information to Tycho,
who then reports to Livia.

43:22.861 --> 43:25.690
She had them
sell you a laxative.

43:47.233 --> 43:50.192
-She's here.
-Is it ready?

43:50.236 --> 43:51.846
The Greek redid the seal
with the new ring.

43:55.067 --> 43:55.720
Wait for me outside.

44:10.735 --> 44:13.433
[exhales]

44:21.702 --> 44:25.358
That's the will of Augustus.

44:25.401 --> 44:26.751
Take it.

44:30.624 --> 44:32.060
You didn't read it?

44:32.104 --> 44:35.063
Not yet, no.

44:35.107 --> 44:38.240
What did you want it for,
anyway?

44:38.284 --> 44:42.723
Well, I wanted to know
what's in it for me.

44:44.594 --> 44:47.293
I accept your terms.

44:51.123 --> 44:54.474
My clerks will arrange
the paperwork.

44:59.784 --> 45:02.308
Have it sent to my summer
residence on the lake.

45:02.351 --> 45:05.224
I'm going there tomorrow.

45:05.267 --> 45:06.878
One more thing.

45:10.620 --> 45:11.709
I'm sorry...

45:15.321 --> 45:17.453
...for everything.

45:22.894 --> 45:27.072
I couldn't give Gaius children,
so, you know,

45:27.115 --> 45:32.120
I had to prove myself
in other ways.

45:32.164 --> 45:35.602
With him,
you always have to do that.

45:35.645 --> 45:38.344
I owe you that.

45:40.825 --> 45:43.479
We were friends.

45:43.523 --> 45:45.612
I loved you.

45:45.655 --> 45:49.529
And I betrayed you.

46:00.583 --> 46:02.716
We won't see each other again,

46:02.760 --> 46:09.157
and so I wanted you to know
that I'm sorry.

46:09.201 --> 46:12.987
Oh, so sorry.

46:13.031 --> 46:15.381
So sorry.

46:21.735 --> 46:26.653
Your mother's bracelets,
I always loved them.

46:26.696 --> 46:28.481
Oh, I remember.

46:28.524 --> 46:31.266
Have them sent down as well.

46:31.310 --> 46:33.703
[sighs]

46:33.747 --> 46:36.706
I lost them...

46:36.750 --> 46:41.146
along with many other things
years ago.

46:44.889 --> 46:50.329
[footsteps receding]

46:50.372 --> 46:52.505
[clinks]

46:52.548 --> 46:57.727
This is the new will.

46:57.771 --> 47:00.513
It's identical in every respect
except for your changes.

47:00.556 --> 47:02.558
Greek's a genius.

47:02.602 --> 47:04.952
Keep it safe.

47:04.996 --> 47:08.042
If anything happens to Gaius,
we need it near.

47:08.086 --> 47:11.263
And the real one will easily
disappear when the time comes.

47:14.875 --> 47:19.227
I don't understand.

47:19.271 --> 47:21.664
You got what you wanted,
your own will of Augustus,

47:21.708 --> 47:24.754
naming Drusus as successor.

47:24.798 --> 47:26.844
You had to pay Turia off,
which is obviously annoying,

47:26.887 --> 47:28.584
but you're still rich.

47:28.628 --> 47:32.284
What she wants,
I can never give her.

47:32.327 --> 47:35.417
Not then, not now.

47:35.461 --> 47:39.769
She will take everything I have,
and it will never be enough.

47:39.813 --> 47:43.208
And in the end
she will go to Gaius,

47:43.251 --> 47:44.731
and he will believe her.

47:44.774 --> 47:46.298
Mm.

47:46.341 --> 47:50.955
And so, everything ends.

47:53.958 --> 47:57.439
The Chief Vestal
is protected by the gods.

47:57.483 --> 48:02.575
She can't even be touched,
let alone harmed or killed.

48:02.618 --> 48:04.882
I won't be part of that,

48:04.925 --> 48:06.579
and neither will
any of the Friends,

48:06.622 --> 48:09.495
not even for you.
-This is her or me, Tycho.

48:09.538 --> 48:12.063
You can't kill someone
without killing them,

48:12.106 --> 48:15.414
especially if you
can't even touch them.

48:15.457 --> 48:18.460
It won't be easy,

48:18.504 --> 48:22.421
but she's going
to the lake tomorrow.

48:22.464 --> 48:24.989
[exhales]

48:25.032 --> 48:27.643
Here's how we do it.

48:30.037 --> 48:40.613
[music playing,
vocalizing]

48:40.656 --> 48:46.619
[sobbing]

48:46.662 --> 48:56.107
♪♪♪

48:56.150 --> 49:01.547
♪♪♪

49:14.038 --> 49:16.040
She's off to the lake.

49:20.392 --> 49:21.871
Get everyone ready.

49:33.535 --> 49:37.844
♪♪♪

49:37.887 --> 49:40.760
[breathing heavily]

49:44.764 --> 49:48.637
This is Livia, daughter
of Marcus Livius Drusus.

49:48.681 --> 49:51.336
[breathing heavily]

49:51.379 --> 49:54.208
I ask your forgiveness

49:54.252 --> 49:56.036
as I defend myself

49:56.080 --> 50:01.999
against the unjust vengeance
of your servant, Turia.

50:02.042 --> 50:06.655
She has dishonored her Order

50:06.699 --> 50:09.180
and betrayed your trust.

50:09.223 --> 50:12.400
So, now I do what I must,

50:12.444 --> 50:16.404
and I ask you all
for your understanding.

50:19.799 --> 50:21.583
In return, after my death,

50:21.627 --> 50:27.850
I will build a temple
to all the gods,

50:27.894 --> 50:31.506
the greatest ever seen on Earth.

50:31.550 --> 50:34.466
♪♪♪

50:56.140 --> 50:57.097
[grunts]

51:03.625 --> 51:04.496
[horse whinnies]

51:10.154 --> 51:12.069
Easy.

51:21.513 --> 51:22.514
[Turia] Hey...

51:28.433 --> 51:30.348
Hey!

51:33.307 --> 51:36.310
-[banging]
-Let me out!

51:36.354 --> 51:38.138
Hey, Quintus!

51:45.232 --> 51:47.321
What is this?!

51:47.365 --> 51:49.497
-Come on.
-[Turia] Who are you?!

51:49.541 --> 51:50.803
Let me out!

51:50.846 --> 51:52.674
[Tycho] Get that carriage
off the road.

51:52.718 --> 51:56.809
[breathing heavily]

51:56.852 --> 52:01.640
♪♪♪

52:01.683 --> 52:03.816
No! Wait!

52:03.859 --> 52:05.339
Let me out!

52:05.383 --> 52:07.994
This is sacrilege!

52:10.039 --> 52:13.565
[Turia shouting indistinctly]

52:16.524 --> 52:19.745
[screams]

52:19.788 --> 52:23.140
[continues
shouting indistinctly]

52:23.183 --> 52:26.708
Wall it up. Nobody gets in.

52:26.752 --> 52:30.799
Nobody gets out. Ever.

52:30.843 --> 52:35.195
♪♪♪

52:35.239 --> 52:38.851
[Turia] No!

52:38.894 --> 52:43.682
No!

52:43.725 --> 52:51.951
♪♪♪

52:53.735 --> 52:55.215
No!

52:55.259 --> 52:59.045
♪♪♪

52:59.088 --> 53:02.179
No!

53:02.222 --> 53:05.704
Do you know who I am?!

53:05.747 --> 53:15.757
♪♪♪

53:15.801 --> 53:17.759
[whispers] Livia...

53:20.458 --> 53:26.072
[whispers] Livia...

53:26.115 --> 53:29.815
Livia!

53:31.512 --> 53:33.906
[sniffles, whimpers]

53:38.911 --> 53:41.914
Untouched?

53:41.957 --> 53:43.481
Unharmed?

53:46.484 --> 53:48.137
You were right.

53:48.181 --> 53:51.228
The cave is remote.

53:51.271 --> 53:52.925
How did you know it was there?

53:52.968 --> 53:57.756
We used to play inside
when we were children.

53:57.799 --> 53:59.671
Me and Turia.

54:03.501 --> 54:05.111
Do you think
they'll let this go?

54:05.154 --> 54:06.547
Who?

54:06.591 --> 54:09.202
The gods?

54:12.814 --> 54:14.512
We'll find out.

54:23.869 --> 54:27.481
Go get the priestess Aurelia.

54:27.525 --> 54:31.050
I want a copy
of Agrippa's will, too.

55:10.089 --> 55:12.570
-[Tycho] I love you.
-[giggles]

55:44.036 --> 55:45.559
Livia?

55:45.603 --> 55:47.692
Can I stay?

55:51.304 --> 55:53.959
I don't want to be alone.

56:35.000 --> 56:37.916
[theme music playing]
